Uploaded patch set 46: New patch set was added with same tree, parent tree, and commit message as Patch Set 45.

For the "port number is null when service disabled" issue, it can be solved by calling service-config-manager to get the service info instead of calling systemd

Pros:
* Can get port number when service disabled
* Setting service enable/port will reflect immediately on redfish

Cons:
* It represents the configured status, not real status. e.g. Disabling service via systemctl will not 
make redfish to show ServiceEnabled==false unless service-config-manager restarts.
